# CSS Theme Variables Rule

## Use Theme Inline Variables Instead of CSS Variables

When using Tailwind CSS classes with theme colors, always use theme inline variables with opacity modifiers instead of CSS variable syntax.

### ❌ BAD - Don't use this pattern:
```tsx
className="bg-[var(--background)]/80"
className="border-[var(--border)]/50"
className="text-[var(--foreground)]"
className="hover:bg-[var(--hover)]/50"
```

### ✅ GOOD - Use theme inline variables:
```tsx
className="bg-background/80"
className="border-border/50"
className="text-foreground"
className="hover:bg-hover/50"
```

### Available Theme Variables:
- `background` / `bg-background`
- `foreground` / `text-foreground`
- `muted` / `bg-muted`
- `muted-foreground` / `text-muted-foreground`
- `border` / `border-border`
- `accent` / `bg-accent`
- `accent-foreground` / `text-accent-foreground`
- `card` / `bg-card`
- `card-foreground` / `text-card-foreground`
- `hover` / `bg-hover`
- `input` / `bg-input`
- `input-border` / `border-input-border`
- `input-focus` / `border-input-focus`

### Opacity Modifiers:
All theme colors support Tailwind's opacity modifiers (e.g., `/50`, `/80`, `/30`):
- `bg-background/80` - 80% opacity
- `border-border/50` - 50% opacity
- `bg-hover/50` - 50% opacity

This ensures consistency with Tailwind CSS v4's theme system and proper theme-aware styling.
